T1  - Minds and Managers: On the Dual Nature Of Human Information Processing And Management, 
AU  - Taggart, William
AU  - Robey, Daniel
Y1  - 1981/04/01
PY  - 1981
DA  - 1981/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1981.4287774
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1981.4287774
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 187
EP  - 195
VL  - 6
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - In this paper we present a concept of dual human information processing as an aid to understanding the decision styles and decision strategies of managers. Several threads of thought are woven together: neurological studies of ?split-brain? persons, Jung's typology of personality, and philosophical explanations of human duality. The resulting framework differentiates a range of left- to right-hemisphere-dominant decision styles and integrates four decision strategies expressed as approaches to the person and the environment.
AB  - In this paper we present a concept of dual human information processing as an aid to understanding the decision styles and decision strategies of managers. Several threads of thought are woven together: neurological studies of ?split-brain? persons, Jung's typology of personality, and philosophical explanations of human duality. The resulting framework differentiates a range of left- to right-hemisphere-dominant decision styles and integrates four decision strategies expressed as approaches to the person and the environment.
