T1  - An MCDM Approach for Resolving Goal Conflict in MBO
AU  - Barton, Richard F.
Y1  - 1981/04/01
PY  - 1981
DA  - 1981/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1981.4287799
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1981.4287799
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 231
EP  - 241
VL  - 6
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Management by objectives tends to focus on one goal or objective at a time or on goals that can be made consistent. Little attention in either literature or practice is given to goals that are to be achieved simultaneously, yet conflict. Recent work in multiple-criteria decision making (MCDM) can help in the formulation of goal-conflict decisions in MBO contexts. Techniques for resolving conflicts between persons can be incorporated in an MCDM framework that explicates conflict among simultaneous goals and reveals value conflicts between managers and subordinates.
AB  - Management by objectives tends to focus on one goal or objective at a time or on goals that can be made consistent. Little attention in either literature or practice is given to goals that are to be achieved simultaneously, yet conflict. Recent work in multiple-criteria decision making (MCDM) can help in the formulation of goal-conflict decisions in MBO contexts. Techniques for resolving conflicts between persons can be incorporated in an MCDM framework that explicates conflict among simultaneous goals and reveals value conflicts between managers and subordinates.
