TY  - JOUR
T1  - Corporate Strategy and Executive Action: Transition Stages and Linkage Dimensions
AU  - Camillus, John C.
Y1  - 1981/04/01
PY  - 1981
DA  - 1981/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1981.4287821
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1981.4287821
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 253
EP  - 259
VL  - 6
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The metamorphosis of corporate strategy into operating decisions and actions has been analyzed in the policy, planning, and control literature. In this article, I integrate these perspectives into a framework that defines the stages in the transition from strategy to action as (1) business strategy, (2) action planning, (3) budgeting, and (4) executive action, for the single-business organization. For the multibusiness organization, there is an additional stage, corporate strategy, which precedes the other four. These transition stages are linked by structure, process, and content.
